The paper discusses the analysis and improvement of pseudorandom number generators, which falls under the category of probability and statistics (cs.PR). The paper also explores the space of possible generators and their parameters, which involves data structures (cs.DS) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The use of statistical tests and the evaluation of the quality of the generators falls under the category of data mining (cs.DM). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the generators, which involves programming languages and compilers (cs.PL).
